      <div class="js-dropdown-content about-content hidden">
        <p class="padding-top-m"><b>Job Description</b></p>
        <p>
          The opportunity is for a detail and design oriented person with strong 
          communication skills. Our focus is on creating unique pieces that are accessible 
          jewelry. We strive to achieve this vision primarily through our creative and enthusiastic employees 
          who dare to be innovative, and thrive in a friendly and fast-paced environment. 
          The position will include accountabilities including prototype, file creation, 
          communication, support for cross functional partners, and collaboration.
        </p>
        <p><b>Details</b></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Coordinate prototype fabrication and installation activities to ensure products 
            and systems conform to engineering design and specification. Evaluate and recommend 
            design modifications.</li>
          <li>Work on multiple projects simultaneously and meet tight deadlines within established budgets.</li>
          <li>Collaborate effectively with design and production team members.</li>
          <li>Prepare drawings consisting of standard arrangements, layouts, flow sheets, assemblies, 
            isometrics, etc., from rough sketches and/or from general engineering and design information 
            according to established standards and procedures.</li>
          <li>Works closely with other Designer/Drafters to ensure a coordinated design.</li>
          <li>Compiles data and performs dimensional and routine tasks required for the preparation of drawings.</li> 
          <li>Reads and understands orthographic (2D) and/or isometric (3D) designs and supplier/manufacturer drawings.</li>
          <li>Makes required changes, additions, and/or revisions, as directed by immediate supervisor.
          <li>Oversee junior designer/drafters. Checks drawings prepared by lower-level Designer/Drafters for accuracy and adequacy.</li>
        </ul><br>
        <p><b>Qualifications</b></p>
        <ul>
          <li>Bachelor’s Degree in Jewelry design, fashion design, industrial or product design, fine art or related degree preferred.</li>
          <li>3-5 years of experience using CAD software (at least 3 year Solid Works) to create 3D models and drawings.</li>
          <li>Knowledge of 3D CAD (Rhino, Freeform or similar).</li>
          <li>Proficiency in Photoshop and Illustrator is essential.</li>
          <li>Strong and accurate technical drawing and hand sketching abilities.</li>
          <li>Highly developed visual communication skills, rendering, and quick visualizing. Should be able to visualize in 3D from multiple angles for accurate side and back 
            views when creating spec sheets.</li>
		  <li>Must be a handcraft oriented person and must be skilled in jewelry design by 
            hand and basic jewelry techniques.</li>
          <li>Highly responsible, self-motivated and able to thrive in an energetic, fast-paced, creative team environment.</li>
          <li>Requirements include PC literacy, proficiency in utilizing CAD and other computer software used to complete design assignments.</li>
          <li>Highly developed visual communication skills: sketching, rendering, quick visualizing.</li>
        </ul>
